Notes:
1.{{note|6}} described by Ancient Egyptians as a "hairy star accompanying Pepi I Meryre to the heavens"- possibly an appearance of Comet Hale-Bopp
2.{{note|7}} May have been a sighting of Messier 41.
3.{{note|2}}{{note|3}}{{note|4}}{{note|5}}{{note|8}}{{note|9}}{{note|10}}{{note|11}} Comet later disintegrated.
4.{{note|1}} possibly an appearance of 153P/Ikeya–Zhang
